  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Accountability gaps in enterprise AI programs rarely stem from a lack of policy — they emerge when policies have no named owners. A data steward is the person who holds day-to-day responsibility for the accuracy, completeness, access control, and lifecycle of a specific data asset. In AI and GenAI systems, where the quality of training data, grounding corpora, and embedding indexes directly determines model output quality, steward roles must be defined with precision before deployment begins."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Without clear steward assignments, AI incidents become finger-pointing exercises: the ML team blames stale RAG data, the data engineering team blames unclear quality requirements, and compliance blames the absence of consent records. A well-designed stewardship model prevents this by assigning unambiguous accountability to named individuals for each class of AI data asset."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why It Matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "GenAI systems depend on three categories of data that existing IT stewardship models were not designed to cover: prompt libraries and system prompts (which shape model behavior), grounding corpora used in retrieval-augmented generation, and fine-tuning or RLHF datasets. Each carries distinct risks if mismanaged. Stale grounding data produces confident but incorrect answers. Poorly curated fine-tuning sets introduce bias or leak confidential content. Prompt templates without a steward evolve without review and may drift out of alignment with policy."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Regulators are also paying attention. The EU AI Act's requirements for high-risk AI systems include data governance provisions that implicitly require responsible parties for training and operational data. Without a stewardship model, organizations cannot demonstrate compliance in an audit."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Core Steward Roles"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Stewardship hierarchy: CDO accountable at top, Domain / Technical / AI-ML stewards responsible at second tier, specific accountability areas at bottom"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Domain Data Steward"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Owns all data assets within a specific business domain (e.g., Customer, Product, Finance). For AI systems that operate within that domain, the domain steward approves which data is eligible for training or RAG grounding, validates that data definitions match business intent, and signs off on data classification labels. They are the first escalation path when an AI system produces domain-incorrect outputs."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Technical Data Steward"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Owns pipeline integrity, schema conformance, data quality SLAs, and metadata standards for the data assets in their scope. In GenAI contexts, they manage the ETL/ELT jobs that populate vector indexes, monitor freshness and completeness, and operate the tooling (Great Expectations, dbt tests, etc.) that validates data before it reaches the AI layer."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "AI/ML Data Steward"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A role specific to organizations with material AI workloads. Responsible for the governance of assets that exist only because of AI: prompt templates, embedding model configurations, fine-tuning datasets, RLHF annotation sets, and RAG corpus curation rules. This steward bridges the gap between the domain steward (who owns source business data) and the ML engineer (who builds the model)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "RACI Accountability Framework"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The RACI matrix makes roles explicit and prevents the common failure mode of every team assuming another team is accountable. For each AI data asset, exactly one person is Accountable (the A), one or more are Responsible (do the work), and others are Consulted or Informed."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Example RACI for RAG grounding corpus\nasset: customer-knowledge-base\ntype: rag-grounding-corpus\n\nraci:\n  accountable:\n    role: Domain Data Steward - CX Domain\n    name: Jane Smith\n    email: jane.smith@example.com\n\n  responsible:\n    - role: Technical Data Steward\n      tasks: [pipeline-ops, quality-monitoring, index-refresh]\n    - role: AI/ML Data Steward\n      tasks: [chunking-strategy, embedding-model-selection, relevance-testing]\n\n  consulted:\n    - role: Legal / Privacy\n      trigger: new-data-source-onboarding\n    - role: ML Engineering\n      trigger: embedding-model-change\n\n  informed:\n    - role: CDO\n      cadence: quarterly-review\n    - role: Product Owner\n      trigger: quality-sla-breach\n\n# Review cycle\nreview_cadence: monthly\nescalation_path: [technical-steward, domain-steward, CDO]\nlast_reviewed: 2026-07-01\nnext_review: 2026-08-01"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How the Accountability Framework Works"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The framework operates through a combination of assignment, tooling, and process. Each AI data asset is registered in a data catalog (Collibra, Alation, DataHub, or equivalent) with its steward assignments captured as metadata. A governance calendar schedules recurring review tasks for each steward. When quality SLAs are breached or a new AI model deployment touches a data asset, the stewardship record determines who is notified and who must sign off."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Escalation paths are defined hierarchically: the Technical Data Steward resolves pipeline-level issues within their SLA (typically 4 hours for Tier 1 assets). If unresolved, the Domain Data Steward escalates. The CDO is reserved for cross-domain conflicts or regulatory queries. This hierarchy ensures that no incident stays unresolved because ownership is ambiguous."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Architecture"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Stewardship metadata integrates with the data catalog, the CI/CD pipeline, and the AI model registry:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Registering a data asset with steward assignments\n# Uses a hypothetical data catalog SDK pattern\n\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import List, Optional\nfrom datetime import date\n\n@dataclass\nclass StewardAssignment:\n    role: str\n    name: str\n    email: str\n    tasks: List[str] = field(default_factory=list)\n\n@dataclass\nclass DataAssetGovernance:\n    asset_id: str\n    asset_name: str\n    asset_type: str  # e.g. 'rag-corpus', 'fine-tune-dataset', 'prompt-library'\n    accountable: StewardAssignment\n    responsible: List[StewardAssignment]\n    consulted: List[str]\n    informed: List[str]\n    review_cadence_days: int = 30\n    last_reviewed: Optional[date] = None\n\n    def is_review_due(self) -> bool:\n        if self.last_reviewed is None:\n            return True\n        from datetime import date, timedelta\n        return date.today() >= self.last_reviewed + timedelta(days=self.review_cadence_days)\n\n    def escalation_path(self) -> List[str]:\n        # Returns ordered list of escalation contacts\n        path = [r.email for r in self.responsible]\n        path.append(self.accountable.email)\n        return path\n\n# Example usage\nasset = DataAssetGovernance(\n    asset_id=\"cust-kb-v2\",\n    asset_name=\"Customer Knowledge Base\",\n    asset_type=\"rag-corpus\",\n    accountable=StewardAssignment(\n        role=\"Domain Data Steward\",\n        name=\"Jane Smith\",\n        email=\"jane.smith@example.com\"\n    ),\n    responsible=[\n        StewardAssignment(\n            role=\"Technical Data Steward\",\n            name=\"Bob Lee\",\n            email=\"bob.lee@example.com\",\n            tasks=[\"pipeline-ops\", \"quality-monitoring\"]\n        )\n    ],\n    consulted=[\"legal@example.com\"],\n    informed=[\"cdo@example.com\"],\n    review_cadence_days=30,\n    last_reviewed=date(2026, 7, 1)\n)\n\nif asset.is_review_due():\n    print(f\"Review due for {asset.asset_name}\")\n    print(f\"Escalation path: {asset.escalation_path()}\")"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to Use Formal Steward Roles"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Formal steward role assignments are warranted for: any AI system processing personal data, RAG corpora with more than one contributing source team, fine-tuning datasets derived from production data, and any model deployed in a regulated industry. For internal prototype projects using only synthetic data, a lighter assignment (single owner in a README) may suffice — but should be formalized before production deployment."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Avoid stewardship theater: assigning roles without providing the time, tooling, and authority to act on them. A steward without access to the data catalog, without budget for remediation, and without authority to block a model release is a compliance fig leaf, not a governance control."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Implementation Steps"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Inventory all AI data assets: training sets, grounding corpora, prompt libraries, embedding configs."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Map each asset to a business domain and identify the domain owner."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Define the three steward roles (Domain, Technical, AI/ML) and assign named individuals."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Register assignments in the data catalog with effective date and review cadence."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Configure alerting so stewards are notified automatically on quality SLA breaches."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Run the first steward review within 30 days of assignment to validate completeness."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Document escalation paths and test them with a tabletop exercise before production launch."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Real-World Example"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A financial services firm deploying a GenAI advisor chatbot identified six data assets requiring stewardship: regulatory FAQ corpus, product terms database, customer transaction history (for personalization), system prompt library, embedding model config, and RLHF annotation set. They assigned domain stewards from the Legal and Product teams for the first two, a Privacy Steward for transaction history, and an AI/ML Steward for the last three. The CDO was accountable across all six. When the embedding model changed three months after launch, the AI/ML Steward's sign-off was required before re-indexing — catching a chunking configuration error that would have degraded retrieval precision by 18%."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common Mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The most common mistake is conflating the data owner (a senior business executive who sets policy) with the data steward (the practitioner who executes it). Owners rarely have time for day-to-day stewardship tasks. Assigning a VP as the data steward for a RAG corpus guarantees the role will be neglected."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A second mistake is defining steward responsibilities in a policy document but not connecting them to tooling. If the steward must manually log into a dashboard to check quality metrics, the review cadence will slip. Stewardship works when automated alerts push to the steward, not when the steward must pull."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best Practices"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "One accountable person per asset — not a team or committee."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Stewards must have direct system access: catalog write permissions, pipeline dashboards, alert subscriptions."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Include steward assignments in the AI system card and model card for every deployed model."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Tie steward review completion to the model's deployment gate in CI/CD."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Run quarterly cross-steward calibration sessions to align quality standards across domains."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Capture steward decisions (approve / reject / defer) in the catalog with timestamps for audit."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Performance and Scalability"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "As the number of AI data assets grows, manual steward assignment becomes a bottleneck. Organizations with more than 50 AI data assets should invest in: automated asset discovery (catalog crawlers that detect new vector indexes or fine-tune datasets), role-based default assignments (any new asset in the CX domain defaults to the CX domain steward), and delegation rules (stewards can delegate specific tasks to deputies with time-limited authority)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A common scaling pattern is to create Steward Councils: groups of stewards from related domains who share tooling, calibration meetings, and escalation paths, reducing per-steward overhead while maintaining individual accountability."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Tooling and Ecosystem"
          }
        ]
